                      <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                        <locus from="1r" to="22v"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1758Lefafa">Lǝfāfa ṣǝdq</title>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                          <locus from="1r" to="5v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Prologue</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>After the prologue (<bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">61</citedRange></bibl>), the text follows up to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">63 l. 8</citedRange></bibl>. The following series of names is then omitted, except for two names: those of Bǝrhānāʾel and 
                            Bǝrkoryos, to whom the remission of the sins is asked. 
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                          <locus from="6r" to="7v"/>
                          <title type="complete">ጸሎት፡ በእንተ፡ ፃዕረ፡ ሞት፡</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the first part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">67</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                          <locus from="8r" to="12r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Third section</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the remaining part of the third section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">68 ll. 1-9</citedRange></bibl>, then, after few words, <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">70 l. 5-71 l. 2</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                          <locus from="12r" to="17v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fourth section</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The text contains the fourth section of E.A.W. Budge's edition, corresponding to <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">73 l. 2-75 l. 6</citedRange></bibl>.</note>  
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5">
                          <locus from="17v" to="18r"/>
                          <title type="complete">First prayer for the heavenly journey, entitled ጸሎተ፡ መንገደ፡ ሰማይ፡</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>Short prayer, beginning nearly like in <ref type="item" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet115#ms_i1.14.2"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: BAVet115#ms_i1.14.2</span></ref>.</note>
                          <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                            መሀረኒ፡ ወተሣሃለኒ፡ <surplus>ወ</surplus>ክርስቶስ፡ አምላኪየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ <choice><sic>ታአስ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ታኦስ፡</corr></choice> 
                            ሮቤባዊ፡ ታቦራዊ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ዕዳየ፡ ለገብርከ።
                          </explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.6">
                          <locus from="18r" to="18v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Second prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer begins like in <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">76 ll. 6-7</citedRange></bibl>, then it continues like follows: <q xml:lang="gez">ሚካኤል፡ ወገብርኤል፡ ሱራፌል፡ ወኪሩቤል፡ ይትባደሩ፡ ፍጡነ፡
                            <choice><sic>ወያንሥእዋ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወይንሥእዋ፡</corr></choice> ለነፍስየ፡ ወኢያእምርዋ፡ ፀዋጋን፡ መላእክት፡
                            <gap reason="omitted" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> ከመ፡ ያንብብዋ፡ በደኃሪት፡ ዕለት፡ ለዓ<supplied reason="explanation">ለመ፡</supplied>፡ ዓለም፡</q>.
                          </note>                          
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.7">
                          <locus from="18v" to="19r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Third prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ከመ፡ <choice><sic>ትፈንው</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ትፈንዉ፡</corr></choice> ሊተ<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> 
                              ምሕረተክሙ፡ <choice><sic>ወክነፊክሙ፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">በክነፊክሙ፡</corr></choice> መላእክተ፡ 
                              ምሕረት<supplied reason="omitted">፡ </supplied> <gap reason="omitted" resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices"/> ከመ፡ ትምሀረኒ፡ ወትሣሃለኒ፡ 
                              ወትስ<surplus>፡</surplus>ረይ፡ ኃጢአትየ፡ ለገብር፡
                              </q>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.8">
                          <locus from="19r" to="20r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fourth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>Cp.  <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">76 ll. 14-22</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.9">
                          <locus from="20r" to="21r"/>
                          <title type="complete">Fifth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>The prayer includes the following invocation:
                            <q xml:lang="gez">
                              ወኢይነፅርዋ፡ በመዓልት፡ ወበሌሊት፡ ወኢያንብርዋ፡ ውስተ፡ ደይን፡ <choice><sic>በደኀረት፡</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">በደኀሪት፡</corr></choice> 
                              ዕለት፡ ወይትነሥኡ፡ መላእክት፡ በበ፯ ማዕጠንት<supplied reason="omitted">፡</supplied> ወበበ፯ መዓርጋት፡ ወበበ፯ መናብርት፡
                              <choice><sic>ወበበጊ</sic><corr resp="bm:GrebTiss1935Codices">ወበበ፯</corr></choice> አፍላጋት፡ ወበበ፯ ሰማያት። ይሴብሑ፡ ወይዜምሩ፡                             
                            </q>.
                          </note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.10">
                          <locus from="21v" to="22v"/>
                          <title type="complete">Sixth prayer</title>
                          <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                          <note>Cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/NS8WNSR6"><seg type="book"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Budge1929"/><title level="m">The Bandlet of Righteousness, an Ethiopian Book of the Dead: The Ethiopic Text of the ልፋፈ፡ ጽድቅ፡ in Facsimile from Two Manuscripts in the British Museum</title><title level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Ernest Alfred Wallis</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Budge</t:surname></author><pubPlace>London</pubPlace><publisher>Luzac &amp; Company</publisher><date>1929</date><series><t:title xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" level="s">Luzac’s Semitic Text &amp; Translation Series</t:title><t:biblScope xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" unit="volume">19</t:biblScope></series><biblScope unit="volume">19</biblScope><citedRange unit="page">77 ll. 1-16</citedRange></bibl>, with few additions.</note>
                          <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                            ወኀበ፡ ሀለወት፡ ዛቲ፡ ጸሎት፡ ይሰደዱ፡ አጋንንት፡ በከመ፡ ተሰዱ፡ እመንበረ፡ ስብሐቲሁ፡ ከማሁ፡ ስድዶሙ፡ ለአጋንንት፡ እምላዕለ፡ ገብርከ፨
                          </explicit>
                        </msItem>
                      </msItem>  
                    </msContents>
                  
